Feature: Firmware update on device

  As a Device Builder team
  We want to verify that a device can be updated to the target firmware version
  So that the device remains operational and consistent after update, reboot, reset, hard reset, and power cycle operations

  Background:
    Given the test environment is ready
    And I am logged in to IED and IEM
    And the device is activated
    And the target firmware version is available in IEM

  @software_update @regression
  Scenario: Device can be updated to the target firmware version incrementally
    Given the current device details are captured for firmware update
    When I request an incremental firmware update to the target version
    Then the firmware update should complete successfully
    And the device should reboot and become reachable
    And I restore the IED session
    And edge core should be running
    And the device should remain activated
    And the device firmware version should be the target version

  @software_update @reboot @regression
  Scenario: Device remains operational after reboot following a successful firmware update
    Given the device has been successfully updated to the target firmware version
    When I reboot the device via IED
    Then the device should reboot and become reachable
    And edge core should be running
    And the device should remain activated
    And the device firmware version should still be the target version

  @software_update @reset @regression
  Scenario: Device can be reset after a successful firmware update
    Given the device has been successfully updated to the target firmware version
    When I reset the device via IED
    Then the device should become reachable
    And I restore the IED session
    And edge core should be running
    And the device should remain activated
    And the application count should be 0
    And the device firmware version should still be the target version

  @software_update @hard_reset @regression
  Scenario: Device can be hard reset after a successful firmware update
    Given the device has been successfully updated to the target firmware version
    And the current device details are captured for hard reset
    When I hard reset the device via IED
    Then the device should reboot and become reachable
    And the device should be deactivated
    And the device name should be available in IEM
    And the device firmware version should still be the target version

  @software_update @hard_reset @powercut @regression
  Scenario: Device remains consistent after power cycle following hard reset on an updated device
    Given the device has been successfully updated to the target firmware version
    And the device has been hard reset successfully
    And the device is deactivated
    And the device name is available in IEM
    And I am logged in to the power controller
    When I power off the device
    Then the device should be powered off
    When I power on the device
    Then the device should become reachable
    And the device should remain deactivated
    And the device name should still be available in IEM
    And the device firmware version should still be the target version
